                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d859">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1123R27/14: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-12-13T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 13, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 13—11:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>431. Am ordering Spiker<note n="59" xml:id="d859fn59">Clarence J. Spiker, vice
                        consul, detailed to Peking.</note> to Shanghai to ascertain whether it is
                    possible to secure arrest of Chang Ching Yao reported to be there and have him
                    tried by Mixed Court on the charge of refusing protection in Reimert case.
                    Definite knowledge of his whereabouts will at least make it possible for the
                    Minister to demand that he be apprehended and tried by the Government of China.
                    As Chinese officials are indifferent, some step of this kind is positively
                    necessary to prestige of the United States. Instructions are desired.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
